Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the
boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Coat the @British pork loin steaks{2} with half the garlic and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} on both sides.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Trim the @pak choi{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced widthways), then thinly slice
widthways. Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g}(halved lengthways).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the pork steaks. Fry until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on
each side. Reduce the heat to medium and fry for an additional
~{3-5%minutes}, turning every couple of minutes.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).
Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

When cooked transfer the pork steaks to a clean #plate{} and leave to rest.
Cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out the #frying pan{}.

Pop the now empty #pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once the oil is hot, add the Tenderstem® and pak choi, stir-fry for
~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @ginger puree{15%g}, and remaining garlic, cook for
~{30%seconds}. Add a splash of @water for the sauce{50%ml}, then cover with a
#lid (or #foil{}) and allow to cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Pop the now empty #pan back on medium-high heat.

When the #pan is hot, pour in the @hoisin sauce{32%g}, @teriyaki sauce{75%g}
and water for the sauce, stir and boil until the sauce reduces and thickens,
~{2-4%minutes}.

Slice the pork steak widthways into 1cm thick slices. Add the pork slices to the
sauce and stir to glaze evenly.

Using a #fork{}, gently fluff the rice, then stir through the
@roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Share the sesame rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the steak and sauce.

Serve the ginger veg alongside and sprinkle the spring onion and crushed peanuts
over the dish.

Enjoy!